Product name: Foxtail Barley Ornamental Grass Seeds (Hordeum jubatum) 50Seeds
Description:
Foxtail Barley (Hordeum jubatum) - If you like native ornamental grasses, try growing Foxtail Barley grass seeds. It is also commonly called Squirrel Tail Grass, and it prefers full sun and moist to dry conditions. In the wild, Hordeum jubatum Foxtail Barley can be found growing along the edges of marshes, poorly drained fields, pastures, and gravelly areas along roads and railroads. It even tolerates salt, but it cannot compete well with taller vegetation. Hordeum jubatum has gained popularity as an ornamental grass because of its highly attractive flower heads.
How To Grow Foxtail Barley Seeds: The ornamental grass seeds can be started directly outdoors in spring once frost danger has passed. Prepare a weed free seedbed. Foxtail Barley is known to self-sow easily, but it is shallow-rooted making unwanted seedlings easy to pull and remove.
 Season: Perennial
USDA Zones: 4 - 10
Height: 20 inches

**You can expect that when the paste is removed from the skin, the stain will be a light orange; however, the color will deepen as the pigments are absorbed into the skin. Within 24-48 hours of the removal of the paste, the stain will develop into a rich, dark reddish-brown. The stain will last approximately 1 to 2 weeks, depending on after-care. Naturally, there are variables that will either help develop and maintain the desired results, or prevent effective staining. For best results, paste should be applied to clean skin that is free of lotions or oils. Although the henna is 100% natural and free of harmful chemicals, there are extremely rare instances of allergic reaction to the essential oils. Apply a small amount for a patch-test prior to drawing your design.
**Henna paste can expire if not stored properly. Heat releases the dye content; therefore, henna paste should be stored in the freezer until 30 minutes before use. Henna paste will retain freshness for up to 1 year if stored in the freezer.
The natural henna is a little-known brand that is grown on my friend's family farm and imported from India, which is known to be one of the best regions for henna production. It is a superior quality natural, henna hand-mixed with lemon juice and 100% aromatherapy grade pure essential lavender and eucalyptus oils and tends to produce a consistently dark stain. The henna is filled into this convenient bottle for easy, ready-to-use application. CHEMICAL-FREE.
